SUMMARY:LADR Week 1, Day 2: Subspaces and Combinations
DESCRIPTION:Reading: Axler, Section 1.C.\n\nConceptual Focus: Internalize the three conditions for a subspace (1.34). Understand why a union of subspaces isn't always a subspace, and how "sum" and "direct sum" provide structured ways to combine them.\n\nTool Integration:\n- NotebookLM: Ask it to "Summarize the key differences between a sum of subspaces and a direct sum of subspaces, citing definitions 1.36 and 1.40."\n- Desmos: Plot the subspaces U = span{(1, 2)} and W = span{(-1, 1)} in R². Visualize their sum U+W. Then plot U and the line y=x+1 to see why the latter is not a subspace.\n\nExercises:\n1. 1.C, Ex. 1(a, b)\n2. 1.C, Ex. 10\n3. 1.C, Ex. 12
END:VEVENT
