SUMMARY:LADR Week 1, Day 3: Span & Linear Independence
DESCRIPTION:Reading: Axler, Section 2.A.\n\nConceptual Focus: Master the definitions of linear combination, span, and linear independence. See span as a generative concept and linear independence as an efficiency concept.\n\nTool Integration:\n- Claude: Ask it to "Walk me through the proof of the Linear Dependence Lemma (2.21) in Axler's 'Linear Algebra Done Right', explaining the logic and motivation of each step."\n- Desmos: In R², plot two vectors that are linearly dependent (e.g., u=(1,2) and v=(2,4)). Use sliders to visualize their span. Contrast this with two linearly independent vectors (e.g., u=(1,2) and w=(-1,1)).\n\nExercises:\n1. 2.A, Ex. 1\n2. 2.A, Ex. 6\n3. 2.A, Ex. 11\n4. 2.A, Ex. 14
END:VEVENT
