SUMMARY:LADR Week 1, Day 4: Basis & Dimension
DESCRIPTION:Reading: Axler, Sections 2.B & 2.C.\n\nConceptual Focus: A basis is the "perfect" spanning set. The core insight is that all bases for a space have the same length, which makes the concept of "dimension" well-defined and powerful.\n\nTool Integration:\n- ChatGPT: Ask for a creative analogy for span, linear independence, and basis (e.g., using primary colors, musical notes, or ingredients).\n- NotebookLM: Ask it to "List the key theorems from Sections 2.B and 2.C and provide a one-sentence summary of what each one accomplishes."\n\nExercises:\n1. 2.B, Ex. 3\n2. 2.B, Ex. 8\n3. 2.C, Ex. 1\n4. 2.C, Ex. 12
